---
import DocsLayout from "~/layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CopyableCommand from "~/components/CopyableCommand.astro";
import Callout from "~/components/Callout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Copilot CLI"
  description="How budi tracks GitHub Copilot CLI usage — data sources, what's parsed, and how to verify."
>
  <div class="flex max-w-2xl flex-col gap-10">
    <header>
      <p class="text-fg-dim mb-2 text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase">Provider</p>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">Copilot CLI</h1>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-3 leading-relaxed">
        GitHub Copilot's CLI mode writes local session state files. Budi reads these for token
        counts and model info — no configuration needed beyond installing budi.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="chip border-accent text-accent">Live</span>
        <span class="text-fg-dim text-xs">since v8.4.0</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2 id="data-sources" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Data sources
      </h2>
      <div class="card p-5">
        <h3 id="session-state" class="text-fg mb-1.5 text-sm font-medium">
          Local JSONL session-state (primary)
        </h3>
        <p class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Copilot CLI writes local session state files containing conversation metadata, token
          usage, and model information. Budi auto-discovers and tails these files as they're
          written.
        </p>
        <div class="text-fg-dim mt-3 text-xs">
          <span class="font-medium">Path:</span>
          <code
            class="bg-surface-3 border-line/70 text-fg ml-1 rounded border px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[0.9em]"
            >~/.config/github-copilot/</code
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="what-is-parsed" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        What's parsed
      </h2>
      <ul class="text-fg-muted space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Input and output token counts per message
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Model name and version
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Dollar cost (computed from token counts via budi's pricing manifest)
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Session timestamps
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Working directory context for repo/branch attribution
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="caveats" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Caveats</h2>
      <Callout kind="info" title="Copilot CLI vs Copilot Chat">
        Copilot CLI (the terminal agent invoked with <code
          class="bg-surface-3 border-line/70 text-fg rounded border px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[0.9em]"
          >gh copilot</code
        >) and Copilot Chat (the VS Code sidebar) are tracked separately by budi. Each has its own
        tailer and data source. See <a
          href="/docs/providers/copilot-chat/"
          class="link-underline hover:text-fg">Copilot Chat</a
        > for VS Code specifics.
      </Callout>
      <ul class="text-fg-muted mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Cost is estimated from token counts using budi's pricing manifest. GitHub does not expose a
          per-request billing API for Copilot CLI.
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          The session state format depends on the <code
            class="bg-surface-3 border-line/70 text-fg rounded border px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[0.9em]"
            >gh</code
          > CLI version — keep your GitHub CLI up to date for best compatibility.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="verify" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">How to verify</h2>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        After installing budi, run a Copilot CLI session with <code
          class="bg-surface-3 border-line/70 text-fg rounded border px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[0.9em]"
          >gh copilot</code
        >. Then:
      </p>
      <CopyableCommand command="budi doctor" variant="compact" />
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-4 leading-relaxed">
        Look for the Copilot CLI tailer in the output:
      </p>
      <pre
        class="card mt-3 overflow-x-auto p-5 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed"><code class="text-fg">✓ Daemon running (pid 12345, port 7878)
✓ Copilot CLI tailer: active
  Path: ~/.config/github-copilot/
  Last event: 3s ago
✓ All checks passed.</code></pre>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-4 leading-relaxed">To see Copilot CLI spend:</p>
      <CopyableCommand command="budi stats projects --filter copilot-cli" variant="compact" />
    </section>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
